    },
    {
      "id": "sybil_7_listing_7",
      "firm_id": "sybil_7",
      "description": "Presenting a concours-level 2002 Porsche 911 Carrera 4S. This 996.2 iteration utilizes the 3.6L M96/03 flat-six power plant featuring VarioCam Plus and an integrated dry-sump lubrication system. Power is delivered via a G96/31 6-speed manual gearbox to a permanent four-wheel-drive system. The mechanical integrity is absolute, featuring a proactive LN Engineering IMS Solution and a recent bore-scope inspection confirming pristine cylinder walls. The suspension geometry remains taut, utilizing factory-fresh bushings and McPherson struts. Braking performance is anchored by four-piston monobloc calipers over ventilated, cross-drilled rotors. This vehicle exhibits zero mechanical lash and maintains optimal compression across all cylinders.",
